criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Systemically-healthy partially edentulous patients rehabilitated with functional
             dental implants and prostheses for at least 1 year;

          -  Patients had been diagnosed with peri-implant mucositis, probing depth up to 5 mm,
             bleeding on probing and no radiographic evidence of bone loss beyond the first two
             threads of the implant;

          -  Patients had been diagnosed with gingivitis in homologous teeth to implants.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Non-smokers and not in maintenance therapy;

          -  Periodontal treatment during the last six months;

          -  Have not used antimicrobial (systemic or topical), anti-inflammatory or
             immunosuppressive drugs during the six months preceding the study.
